After a while we realized how loud the place was - we had to shout to have a conversation. That's ok for a club but not for a restaurant. Finally, we were charged a 15% service charge.  I'm not a fan of automatic service charges, and based on the service we received 15% was excessive.  All in all a very disappointing meal.

This is the best BBQ I have had in a long time. The atmosphere is very festive. We had just come from the Apollo Theater and wanted something good to eat. My wife and I ordered the chicken and the ribs with a side order of collard greens and plantains. The portions were hardy. Service was excellent and the prices were reasonable. A definite must go to if you are in Harlem, New York City... Also, get a piece of red velvet cake to go...
